main event: A UFO was observed in Hutchinson, Kansas on December 16, 1963, with radar confirmation and visual sightings.
interesting points: The UFO was reported as having a round shape and was visible for only 1-2 seconds., It was sighted between 0-2 degrees elevation above the horizon and disappeared at 20 degrees., There were intermittent radar blips indicating its presence., Witnesses in moving vehicles observed the object from different angles., The report concluded that the object was unidentified, with possibilities including a balloon or known satellite.
witness description: technical representatives from Hutchinson Air Station, including service members and a civilian.
